# UI/UX Design Guidelines

## Design Philosophy

QickReed uses a **neobrutalism** design system (decision AD-005 in `.specs/STATE.md`). Core principles:

1. **Bold everywhere**: thick black borders, hard shadows, square corners on every surface — including RSVP training and assessment reading screens.
2. **Physical interactions**: elements shift toward their shadow on hover and collapse the offset on active (translate + shadow-to-zero).
3. **Flat fills, no gradients, no blur**: solid backgrounds; shadows are hard offsets (`Npx Npx 0 0 #000`), never blurred.
4. **Two-accent palette**: monochrome base + `#FFD23F` (yellow) and `#FF6B6B` (red, errors only). Success is non-color.
5. **Accessibility**: inclusive design that works for all users (WCAG AA, visible focus, keyboard nav).

DaisyUI is fully removed. Do not reintroduce it or use any DaisyUI component class.

## Token System (`src/app/globals.css`)

All styling is driven by centralized CSS variables so dark mode stays achievable by swapping `:root` values only. Do not hard-code hex colors in components — consume tokens.

```css
:root {
  --black: #000000;     /* text + borders */
  --white: #ffffff;     /* component backgrounds */
  --bg: #ffffff;        /* page background */
  --main: #ffd23f;      /* accent 1: primary / highlights / active */
  --error: #ff6b6b;     /* accent 2: error states only */
  --radius: 0;          /* square corners */

  /* hard offset shadows, zero blur */
  --shadow-brutal: 4px 4px 0px 0px var(--black);
  --shadow-brutal-sm: 3px 3px 0px 0px var(--black);
  --shadow-brutal-lg: 6px 6px 0px 0px var(--black);
}
```

`@theme inline` maps these to Tailwind tokens: `--color-main`, `--color-error`, `--color-bg`, `--radius-brutal` / `--radius-base`, `--shadow-brutal` / `-sm` / `-lg`, plus the Geist font vars. Gray scales (`--color-primary-*`, `--color-secondary-*`, `--color-neutral-*`) remain for text/border utility classes.

Two structural utilities (defined in `globals.css`):

- `focus-brutal` — `&:focus-visible { outline: 3px solid var(--black); outline-offset: 2px; }`
- `transition-brutal` — `transition-property: transform, box-shadow; 150ms ease-in-out`

## Color Palette

| Token | Value | Use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `--black` | `#000000` | Text, 3px borders, shadow color |
| `--white` | `#ffffff` | Component/page backgrounds |
| `--bg` | `#ffffff` | Page background |
| `--main` | `#ffd23f` | Primary actions, highlights, active nav, active states |
| `--error` | `#ff6b6b` | Error alerts/fills only |
| grays (`primary-*`/`neutral-*`) | various | Secondary text, subtle borders |

**Text on accents is always black** (`#FFD23F` ≈ 17:1, `#FF6B6B` ≈ 7.8:1 — both pass AA). Never white-on-accent. **Success has no color** — convey it with an icon + pt-BR text + thick black border (WCAG: not color-only). No green.

## Typography

**Font Stack**: Geist Sans (primary), system fonts fallback.

```css
font-family: var(--font-geist-sans), -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
  sans-serif;
```

## Text Hierarchy

- **H1**: `text-3xl font-bold` (30px, 700 weight, black)
- **H2**: `text-2xl font-semibold` (24px, 600 weight, black)
- **H3**: `text-xl font-medium` (20px, 500 weight, dark gray)
- **Body**: `text-base` (16px, 400 weight, black)
- **Secondary**: `text-gray-600` (16px, 400 weight, medium gray)
- **Small**: `text-sm` (14px, 400 weight, medium gray)
- **Extra Small**: `text-xs` (12px, 400 weight, light gray)

## Components

Components live in two places:

- **neobrutal-ui primitives** (copied via CLI, owned source): `src/components/ui/{button,card,input,textarea,label,checkbox,badge,alert,dialog}.tsx` — themed via `:root` vars, CVA variants.
- **Hand-rolled primitives** (token-driven): `src/components/ui/{select,radio,spinner,table,join,divider,form-control}.tsx`.

**Prefer the shared wrappers** in `src/components/` (`Button.tsx`, `Card.tsx`, `ScrollLockTextArea.tsx`, `QuizQuestion.tsx`, `DeleteTextModal.tsx`, `Sidebar.tsx`, `Timer.tsx`, `RsvpDisplay.tsx`, `RichTextEditor.tsx`) — they delegate to the primitives and preserve stable call-site APIs.

Icons: Heroicons.

### Cards

```tsx
<Card shadow="md" padding="p-6">
  {/* content — shadow prop maps to --shadow-brutal-sm/-/-lg */}
</Card>
```

Renders: 3px black border, square corners, hard offset shadow, white fill.

### Buttons

```tsx
<Button variant="primary" size="md">Save</Button>
<Button variant="secondary" size="md">Cancel</Button>
<Button variant="outline" size="sm">Details</Button>
```

- `primary` — `--main` yellow fill + black text + 3px black border + hard shadow.
- `secondary` — white fill + 3px black border + hard shadow.
- `outline` — transparent, hover/active bg-black/5|10.
- Hover: shift toward shadow (or shadow shrinks to `-sm`). Active: offset collapses + `translate-x/y` by the offset.

### Input / Textarea / Select

```tsx
<Input className="w-full" placeholder="email@example.com" />
<Textarea className="w-full" />
<Select>...</Select>  {/* native <select>, 3px border + shadow-brutal-sm + focus-brutal */}
```

3px black border, square corners, white flat fill, black text, `focus-brutal` outline.

### Labels / Form Control

```tsx
<FormControl>
  <Label htmlFor="email">Email</Label>
  <Input id="email" />
</FormControl>
```

`FormControl` = `flex flex-col gap-2`. `Label` passes `htmlFor` through to the native `<label>`.

### Alert (error / success)

```tsx
<Alert variant="error">Mensagem de erro em pt-BR</Alert>
<Alert variant="success">Operação concluída</Alert>
```

- `error` — `--error` red fill + black text + 3px black border + hard shadow.
- `success` — white fill, check icon, pt-BR text, thick black border (no green).

### Badge

```tsx
<Badge>active</Badge>
```

3px black border, square, flat fill.

### Checkbox / Radio

```tsx
<Checkbox id="terms" />          {/* neobrutal-ui Checkbox (Base UI) */}
<Radio id="opt1" name="quiz" />  {/* native, appearance-none, checked:bg-black */}
```

Native `radio` is hand-rolled (single usage in `QuizQuestion.tsx`).

### Spinner (loading)

```tsx
<Spinner size="md" />  {/* border-[3px] border-black border-r-transparent animate-spin, aria-hidden */}
```

### Table

```tsx
<Table>
  <TableHeader>...</TableHeader>
  <TableBody>...</TableBody>
</Table>
```

`border-collapse`, 3px black cell borders, square.

### Dialog (modal)

```tsx
<Dialog>...</Dialog>  {/* neobrutal-ui Dialog: square, 3px border, hard shadow */}
```

### Join / Divider

```tsx
<Join><Button>Prev</Button><Button>Next</Button></Join>
<Divider>or</Divider>
```

`Join` shares inner borders (`-ml-[3px]` on inner items). `Divider` = 3px black rule, optional label.

## Interactive States

### Focus

Use the `focus-brutal` utility (3px solid black `focus-visible` outline, 2px offset) on every interactive element. Do not rely on color alone.

### Hover / Active (physical)

- **Hover**: element shifts toward the shadow (e.g. `hover:shadow-brutal-sm`) or the shadow shrinks.
- **Active**: shadow offset collapses to `0 0 0 #000` and the element `translate-x/y` by the original offset.
- Use the `transition-brutal` utility (`transform, box-shadow`, 150ms) for the motion.

## Spacing System

Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently:

- **Form fields**: `space-y-6` (1.5rem vertical spacing)
- **Card padding**: `p-6`–`p-8` (1.5–2rem)
- **Section margins**: `mb-8`, `mt-8` (2rem)
- **Element spacing**: `mt-2` (0.5rem)

## Tailwind CSS Standards

- **No DaisyUI** — do not use `btn`, `card`, `card-body`, `input-bordered`, `select-bordered`, `label-text`, `form-control` (as a class), `alert-error`, `modal-box`, `loading-spinner`, `join`, `divider`, `badge`, `range`, `tab`, etc. Use the primitives/wrappers above instead.
- **Border**: `border-[3px] border-black rounded-none` (or the primitives, which apply this).
- **Shadow**: `shadow-brutal` / `shadow-brutal-sm` / `shadow-brutal-lg` (hard offset, zero blur) — never Tailwind's blurred `shadow-sm/md/lg` for primary surfaces.
- **Accent fills**: `bg-main text-black` / `bg-error text-black`.

### Responsive Design

- **Mobile First**: Start with mobile styles
- **Breakpoints**: Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- **Container**: Max width `max-w-md` for forms, `max-w-4xl` for content
- **Tap targets**: ≥44px on mobile

## Accessibility Guidelines

1. **Form Accessibility**: Every form field must have an associated label using `htmlFor`
2. **Required Fields**: Use the `required` attribute for mandatory fields
3. **Focus Indicators**: All interactive elements must have a visible `focus-brutal` state (WCAG 2.4.7)
4. **Color Contrast**: All text must meet WCAG AA — black text on `#FFD23F` (≈17:1) and `#FF6B6B` (≈7.8:1); never white-on-accent
5. **Keyboard Navigation**: Logical tab order through interactive elements
6. **Success not color-only**: convey success with icon + pt-BR text + border, not a green fill

## Future Considerations

### Dark Mode Support

Tokens are centralized in `:root` — a future dark palette is achievable by swapping `:root` values only (no per-component hard-coded colors). Not implemented yet.

### Component Expansion

New components should be added as neobrutal-ui primitives (via `npx neobrutal add <name>`) or hand-rolled token-driven primitives under `src/components/ui/`, and consumed through a wrapper in `src/components/` when reused across pages. All must follow the token system and accessibility requirements above.

---

_This document defines the neobrutalism design system for all development in QickReed (AD-005). Any deviations should be documented and approved._